  <p>
    What the mock/contract schema covers, and where each capability sits. <strong>OpenAPI</strong> = borrowed
    from the OpenAPI substrate (the response shape); <strong>Behavior</strong> = the WE behavior layer OpenAPI
    cannot express; <strong>Interaction</strong> = the consumer-driven (Pact/BDCT) layer that makes the
    artifact contract-bearing; <strong>Provider</strong> = a runtime concern owned by the server/console, not
    the portable artifact.
  </p>
